{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Slot Index","anchor":"Slot-Index"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Valid slot indices have to be in range of 0 ..< ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Whiteboard\/documentation\/Whiteboard\/Whiteboard\/slotCount","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"While a slot index has to be an integer value within that range, it is advisable to use a type-safe alternative in Swift, such as a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RawRepresentable"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enum"},{"text":" whose ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RawValue"},{"text":" represents the corresponding slot index.  This can be achieved by creating an ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"enum"},{"text":" that conforms to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"WhiteboardSlot"},{"text":" protocol, e.g.:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["enum MyWhiteboardSlot: Int, WhiteboardSlot {","    case firstWhiteboardSlot","    case secondWhiteboardSlot","    case thirdWhiteboardSlot","    \/* ... *\/","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This enum can then be passed into the corresponding "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Whiteboard\/documentation\/Whiteboard","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" methods.  However, while less error-prone than using a hard-coded index number, there is still the danger of posting a whiteboard message to the wrong slot.  Strongly typed whiteboard messages are safer and avoid this problem altogether. For details, see:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Whiteboard\/documentation\/Whiteboard\/TypeSafety"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","identifier":{"interfaceLangua